            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2134-Step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2134-Step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rinse the <strong>sushi rice</strong> in a sieve under <strong>cold running water</strong> for 30 secs (use your hands to really wash the grains!), then set aside to drain fully</p>\n<p>Add the<strong> drained rice</strong> with 200ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [400ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\n<p>Tip: Don't let the water fully boil as this will make the rice stick to the pot!</p>",
